Class Event.StringEvent

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.steelypip.powerups.jinxml.Event
      • com.steelypip.powerups.jinxml.Event.LiteralConstantEvent

  • Enclosing class:
    Event

    public static class Event.StringEvent
extends Event.LiteralConstantEvent
    This event corresponds to a string. So in the below example, the first float event would correspond to the underlined text. 
    
 	{ foo: [ 1, 2.0, true, null, "i am string" ] }
                               ^^^^^^^^^^^^^
    The value that is passed to the constructor will have had all escape processing fully applied. Handlers will typically transform handleStringEvent into a pair of handleStartTag handleEndTag calls with the element-name Element.STRING_ELEMENT_NAME.
